data.description: 58 Park is located in Buffalo’s most diverse, eccentric, and walkable neighborhoods, (Josh) Allen-town. Located less than 1 mile from downtown Buffalo, 5 blocks to Buffalo Niagara Medical Corridor, and in the heart of the most vibrant entertainment district in the entire City of Buffalo. In 2018 the entire property was completely renovated from the roof, down to the basement, including every mechanical/plumbing/electrical system. There are (2) 2-bedroom units, and (2) 1-bedroom units and each dwelling has its own gas, electric, hot water, heat, air conditioning, and parking. The apartments feature tall ceilings, recessed lighting, stone countertops, hardwood floors, new solid wood windows, and patio/deck or balcony space. This property is one of the first AirBnB’s in the City of Buffalo with 4 years of track record, 50% 5 star reviews and a 4.5 star overall rating w/ over 750 reviews. Gross Income 2019: $86,367.71, 2020: $65,130.70 (owner lived in one unit), 2021: $96,047.01, 2022: $97,722.47, Year-To-Date (booked earnings): $68,271.00. All FF&E convey with the sale, enjoy the upside in revenue with more attention to detail and more listing platform exposure as a short term rental.
